This paper discusses the use of the softmax function in computer vision tasks and its vulnerability to adversarial examples. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning architectures, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the generation of adversarial examples, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper discusses the properties of the softmax function, which could also place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
